object.customQuery:
SELECT distinct distribution.SystemId, distribution.ParentId, distribution.CMMContainer, distribution.Id, distribution.UpdateCount, distribution.UpdateUser, distribution.UpdateTimestamp, distribution.AddDt, distribution.AddTm, distribution.DeliveryStatus, distribution.SenderName, distribution.SenderEmailAddr, distribution.SenderPhone, distribution.SenderFax, distribution.ReplyToName, distribution.ReplyToEmailAddr, distribution.Subject, distribution.Memo, distribution.Urgency, distribution.RowId 
FROM
 distribution
where cmmcontainer='Distribution' and systemid in (select systemid from advrxxchangedbeans where concat(adddt,addtm)>='$$m_strtdt' and concat(adddt,addtm) <='$$m_Enddt' and
 cmmcontainer='Distribution')

transformations.description: This reusable expression will properly check and format up to 5 dates that may be in the 'YY-MM-DD' format. It assumes that any years before '50 are in the current century, and any years after '50 are in the previous century.
transformations.name: exp_format_dates

fields.name: out_Date1
fields.expression:
IIF(ISNULL(in_Date1), NULL,
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 0, 2) = '00', 
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3, 2) <= '50', TO_DATE(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YY-MM-DD'), TO_DATE('19' || SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YYYY-MM-DD')),
IIF(IS_DATE(v_Date1, 'YYYY-MM-DD') and DATE_COMPARE(in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD')) > 0 , in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD'))))
